# Documentation

## Developing with Nit

### Learning the language

The [[manual]] describe the specification of the language.

The [[FAQ]] contains some cook-book recipes and answers to some other frequent questions.

You can also look at some [[examples of programs|examples]] written in Nit.

### Nit Compiler and Other Tools

The [[tools]] page documents the compiler and the other tools of Nit.

There is also a [[plugin for eclipse|eclipse]] and a [[bundle for vim|vim]].

A Debugger is being developed and can be used with the Interpreter (nit.nit). See the [[debugger|debugger]] page for informations on how to use it.

### Standard Library 

The <a href="stdlib">standard library</a> references built-ins and standard classes.

### Native interface and FFI
 
The page [[Foreign Function Interface|FFI]] describes the latest interface between Nit and C. It allows to implement Nit methods directly in C code, and more.

Using the older [[native interface]] to use C code within a Nit program, in separate files.

Developing Nit [[wrappers for existing C libraries|wrapping C libraries]] to access their features through normal Nit modules.

